Sentencas: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-sigma(BSCF), a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC), was synthesized by polyacrylicacid (PAA) method.
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ

Sentencas: The lattice structures of samples calcined at different temperatures were characterized by XRD.
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ

Sentencas: Shrinkage, porosity and pore size of the porous BSCF as a function of sintering temperature were investigated.
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ

Sentencas: It was found that the cubic perovskite structure could be formed after calcination at 800 degrees C for 2 h, but not well crystallized as seen from some unknown phases, and the pure cubic perovskite structure was formed after calcination at 1 150 degrees C for 2 h. The particle size of BSCF was less than 1 similar to 2 mu m.
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ

Sentencas: The shrinkage of the porous BSCF increased with sintering temperature, but the opposite was true for the porosity.
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ

Sentencas: After sintering at 1 100 CC for 4 It, the porous BSCF was still in an appropriate structure, with porosity of 29% and electrical conductivity above 400 S(.)cm(-1).
Titulo: Synthesis and properties of new cathode material Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-σ
